Table 3. Performance (%) comparison on the real image-based 
cloth-changing datasets Real28, VC-Clothes, LTCC. GS-GSP

module. The ReID backbone is ResNet-50. 'Standard' is the set-
ting where the images in the test set with the same identity and 
camera view are discarded when computing mAP/Rank-1 [54].

Table 4. Performance (%) comparison on the cloth-changing 
dataset LTCC. Such experiment aims to show that our GI-ReID 
can bring gains because of the exploration of gait information, 
rather than simply introducing silhouettes (i.e., human masks). 
The ReID backbone is ResNet-50.

Table 5. Performance (%) comparison on the cloth-changing 
dataset LTCC. Such experiment aims to show that these pure gait 
recognition works can not work well for cloth-changing ReID. The 
ReID backbone is ResNet-50.

Changing' setting means that the images with same identity, camera view and clothes are discarded during the testing.
